    {
      "order": 6,
      "title": "Self-Learning Hooks & PostgreSQL State",
      "description": "RuVector's claim to fame is that it learns from how you use it. The hooks subsystem is where that happens: `hooks.rs` is a Q-learning engine over patterns, vector-embedded memories, trajectories, error sequences, and file-sequence prediction; `hooks_postgres.rs` is the pgvector-backed persistence layer; and `hooks_schema.sql` is the actual eight-table schema (`ruvector_hooks_patterns`, `_memories`, `_trajectories`, `_errors`, `_file_sequences`, `_swarm_agents`, `_swarm_edges`, `_stats`) that the install writes when you opt into the Postgres backend.",
