      "languageLesson": "pgvector extends Postgres with a `vector` column type and ANN operators (`<=>` cosine, `<#>` inner product, `<->` L2). It lets the hooks engine store learned memories as embeddings directly in SQL and recall them with the same WHERE-clause language used for regular columns \u2014 no separate vector store required."
